        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 4:00AM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 400 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
northwest of Tamaha, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Sallisaw...                       Brushy...
Vian...                           Greenleaf State Park...
Marble City...                    Box...
Webbers Falls...                  Cookson...
Brushy Lake State Park...         Mc Key...
Gore...                           Tamaha...
Lake Tenkiller State Park...      Porum...
Warner...

This includes Interstate 40 in Oklahoma between mile markers 276 and
307.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 700 AM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
